(11, 1, '2024-03-30 07:01:42', '2024-03-30 07:01:42', '<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontSize\":\"large\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-large-font-size\"><a href=\"http://localhost/wordpress/uncategorized/bagyangon-falls/\" data-type=\"link\" data-id=\"http://localhost/wordpress/uncategorized/bagyangon-falls/\"><strong>Bagyangon Falls</strong></a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"imageCrop\":false,\"linkTo\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default\"><!-- wp:image {\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipOKxwaG1zRwSUUG_PyMrRPK-F6AmxQflhuOEgYU=s1360-w1360-h1020\" alt=\"\"/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\"><strong>Photo by: Laurence Baylon</strong></figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image --></figure>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>About 8.5 kilometers separate the waterfall’s location in Sitio Bagyangon in Barangay San Luis from Malitbog, Bukidnon’s core. You have to journey for roughly 45 minutes through a rocky riverbed at Sitio Bagyangon and into the narrow end of a deep ravine after spending two hours traveling from Cagayan de Oro City.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The chilly Bagyangon Falls waters fall into a naturally created, chest-deep pool that has developed over time. It also has a distinct ambiance because of the mist that surrounds it because the water must travel 150 meters to reach its base.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontStyle\":\"normal\",\"fontWeight\":\"400\"}},\"fontSize\":\"medium\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\" style=\"font-style:normal;font-weight:400\"><a href=\"http://localhost/wordpress/uncategorized/bagyangon-falls/\" data-type=\"link\" data-id=\"http://localhost/wordpress/uncategorized/bagyangon-falls/\">Read more</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator {\"opacity\":\"css\"} -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-css-opacity\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Tourism', 'About 8.5 kilometers separate the waterfall’s location in Sitio Bagyangon in Barangay San Luis from Malitbog, Bukidnon’s core. You have to journey for roughly 45 minutes through a rocky riverbed at Sitio Bagyangon and into the narrow end of a deep ravine after spending two hours traveling from Cagayan de Oro City.<br>The chilly Bagyangon Falls waters fall into a naturally created, chest-deep pool that has developed over time. It also has a distinct ambiance because of the mist that surrounds it because the water must travel 150 meters to reach its base.', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'tourism', '', '', '2024-04-16 17:10:04', '2024-04-16 17:10:04', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?page_id=11', 0, 'page', '', 0),
