(174, 1, '2024-04-11 13:52:56', '2024-04-11 13:52:56', '<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"left\",\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontStyle\":\"normal\",\"fontWeight\":\"700\"}},\"fontSize\":\"large\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-large-font-size\" id=\"Panalsalan-Falls\" style=\"font-style:normal;font-weight:700\">BAGYANGON WATERFALLS</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"imageCrop\":false,\"linkTo\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default\"><!-- wp:image {\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipOKxwaG1zRwSUUG_PyMrRPK-F6AmxQflhuOEgYU=s1360-w1360-h1020\" alt=\"\"/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\"><strong>Photo by: Laurence Baylon</strong></figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image --></figure>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>About 8.5 kilometers separate the waterfall\'s location in Sitio Bagyangon in Barangay San Luis from Malitbog, Bukidnon\'s core. You have to journey for roughly 45 minutes through a rocky riverbed at Sitio Bagyangon and into the narrow end of a deep ravine after spending two hours traveling from Cagayan de Oro City.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The chilly Bagyangon Falls waters fall into a naturally created, chest-deep pool that has developed over time. It also has a distinct ambiance because of the mist that surrounds it because the water must travel 150 meters to reach its base.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>How to Get to Bagyangon Waterfalls?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To get to Sitio Bagyangon, you must ride a motorcycle from the town of Malitbog. The ride takes forty-five minutes and costs 200 pesos, or $4, each way. There are children willing to lead you to Bagyangon Falls once you get at Sitio Bagyangon. For bringing you there, you might give them two dollars or one hundred pesos. The hike to the falls takes forty-five minutes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In order to get to the falls, you can also cross the river roughly ten times. Its intense mist will make you feel lightheaded. Additionally, you must cross a deep chest of water in order to approach closer. and after that take in the greatest vista of the falls.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Never forget their rule, and please don\'t leave any rubbish behind.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m28!1m12!1m3!1d63131.000917446836!2d124.88919714612885!3d8.529683327227053!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!4m13!3e6!4m5!1s0x32ffc3eebef0a93b%3A0xf338d395a584a333!2sMalitbog%20Municipal%20Hall%20GVMM%2BFG9%20Malitbog%20Bukidnon!3m2!1d8.5337!2d124.8839302!4m5!1s0x32ffc5a23f80b423%3A0x4bebb5636d54be2f!2sBagyangon%20Falls%20Drop%20Off%20Point%2C%20Malitbog%2C%20Bukidnon!3m2!1d8.5435261!2d124.97692789999999!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sph!4v1712842510134!5m2!1sen!2sph\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" referrerpolicy=\"no-referrer-when-downgrade\"></iframe>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Tourism', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '11-revision-v1', '', '', '2024-04-11 13:52:56', '2024-04-11 13:52:56', '', 11, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=174', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
